subSubSection.paragraph:
Description:
Male:
Total length 3.75. Cephalothorax: length 1.50; width 1.0. Carapace glabrous, without pattern, slightly darker in ocular area, thoracic groove very difficult to see (
Fig. 1a
). Sternum glossy, color pale yellow. Precoxal triangles present, more visible on coxae III–IV, slightly darker than sternum (
Fig. 1c
). Coxae without spurs, coxae III–IV with dark marks on the prolateral surface. Endites same color as sternum. Labium black, longer than wide, length ca. 1/2 of endites (
Fig. 1c
). Chelicera: width 0.23, length 0.65; same color as the cephalic region four promarginal and seven retromarginal teeth; fang length 0.42. Eyes: AER straight, PER almost straight in dorsal view (
Fig. 1a
); ALE almost twice as big as AME; posterior eyes subequal in size. Clypeus about 1/2 the diameter of AME. Abdomen: pale yellow; dorsal surface without marking; lateral surface with three black spots longitudinally distributed (
Fig. 1b
); ventral surface with three black spots: near the pedicel, over the epigastric furrow and before the tracheal spiracle (
Fig. 1c
). Legs: light yellow, tibia and metatarsi with a dark ring on its distal portion; leg I and II with two pairs of ventral macrosetae on tibiae and metatarsi; length: I 14.12; II 7.0; III 4.87; IV 8.37; formula I–IV–II–III. Pedipalp: light yellow, bulb reddish (
Figs 1
d–f); length 2.30. Distal portion of bRTA flattened and transparent, bifurcating at the tip (
Fig. 3d
). Bulb: PTV square-shaped, flat and transparent on a ventral view; PTP conical and slender, almost as long as the MA; PTs semitransparent, as long as the PTP (
Fig. 14c
); MA rhomboid distally, projecting retrolaterally (
Figs. 1f
, 
3a
).
